alcatelIND1DcbxMIB.description: This module describes an authoritative enterprise-specific Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) Management Information Base (MIB): For the Birds Of Prey Product Line System Capability Manager, to allow for system control and limitation setting, of different, features through out the system. Capability manager is a centralized process which provides hardware information and capability to other processes. To optimize the system performance , certain features may be configured to a lower than the hardware limit through capability manager. The right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice is reserved. DcbxTrafficFlow.name: DcbxTrafficFlow
DcbxTrafficFlow.description: Indicates the traffic flow 0: Lossy 1: Lossless

DcbxPriorityTCMap.name: DcbxPriorityTCMap
DcbxPriorityTCMap.description: Each group of four octets in this string specify a 32-bit Traffic class ID. The IDs are stored in network byte order; i.e. octet N corresponds to the most significant 8 bits of the ID, and octet N+3 correspond to the least significant 8 bits. The list is large enough to hold 8 TC IDs, one per priority. The first first 4 octets represent the first priority.

DcbxStatus.name: DcbxStatus
DcbxStatus.description: Indicates the dcbx status (could be related to hardware) 0: OK 1: PFC Resources Exhausted 2: PFC TLV Mismatch 3: ETS TLV Mismatch 4: PFC and ETS TLV Mismatch

DcbxActionTaken.name: DcbxActionTaken
DcbxActionTaken.description: Indicates the action taken as a result of DcbxStatus 0: No action taken (dcbx might not be operationaly UP) 1: Restored ETS admin config 2: Restored PFC admin config 3: Disabled PFC 4: Restored ETS and PFC admin config 5: Configured local admin 6: Configured local recommended 7: Configured remote admin 8: Configured remote recommended

DcbxTCsPresent.name: DcbxTCsPresent
DcbxTCsPresent.description: Octet representing the traffic classes present in a particular profile. Each bit represents the presence of the traffic class. The first bit indicates if TC 0 is present, the second bit indicates TC 1, and so forth. Bit value 1 indicates the TC is present. Bit value 0 indicates the TC is not present. Can be used to change the TC numbering.

DcbxVersion.name: DcbxVersion
DcbxVersion.description: Indicates the dcbx version 0: IEEE 1: CEE 2: AUTO

RemoteDcbxVersion.name: RemoteDcbxVersion
RemoteDcbxVersion.description: Indicates the remote dcbx version 0: IEEE 1: CEE 2: AUTO 3: Unknown

alaDcbxDCProfileTable.name: alaDcbxDCProfileTable
alaDcbxDCProfileTable.description: A table of Data Center profiles.

alaDcbxDCPETSTrafficClassesSupported.name: alaDcbxDCPETSTrafficClassesSupported
alaDcbxDCPETSTrafficClassesSupported.description: Indicates the number of traffic classes supported.

alaDcbxDCPPFCCap.name: alaDcbxDCPPFCCap
alaDcbxDCPPFCCap.description: Indicates the number of traffic classes on the local device that may simultaneously have PFC enabled.

alaDcbxDCPPriorityTCMap.name: alaDcbxDCPPriorityTCMap
alaDcbxDCPPriorityTCMap.description: Indicates the priority TC map. All 8 priorities are assigned a TC.

alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPId.name: alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPId
alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPId.description: Identifier of Template DCB profile. Used when creating a new profile. The template profile values will be copied to the new profile.

alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPName.name: alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPName
alaDcbxDCPTemplateDCPName.description: Name of Template DCB profile. Used when creating a new profile. The template profile values will be copied to the new profile.

alaDcbxDCPTCsPresent.name: alaDcbxDCPTCsPresent
alaDcbxDCPTCsPresent.description: Represents the traffic classes present in this particular profile. Can be used to change the TC numbering. For example, a profile with TCs numbered 0, 1, 2, can be changed to 1, 5, 7. The numbering is assigned in increasing order. The number of TCs specified must match the current number of TCs in the profile.

alaDcbxDCP8023xPauseReady.name: alaDcbxDCP8023xPauseReady
alaDcbxDCP8023xPauseReady.description: Makes a profile pause-ready. Can only be set during profile creation. When enabled, the PFC is lossy for all traffic classes in the profile and they cannot be changed to lossless. Applying this profile to a port will allow the port to have 802.2x pause enabled through the interfaces commands. Can be applied to ports with a standard VFC profile. Can be applied to a DCB port only if pfc willing and pfc tlv bits are disabled.

alaDcbxDCPRowStatus.name: alaDcbxDCPRowStatus
alaDcbxDCPRowStatus.description: alaDcbxDCPRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in the table.

alaDcbxDCPTrafficClassTable.name: alaDcbxDCPTrafficClassTable
alaDcbxDCPTrafficClassTable.description: A table of Traffic Classes for the DCB Profiles.

alaDcbxDCPTCEntry.name: alaDcbxDCPTCEntry
alaDcbxDCPTCEntry.description: A DCB profile traffic class entry.

alaDcbxDCPTCMaximumBandwidth.name: alaDcbxDCPTCMaximumBandwidth
alaDcbxDCPTCMaximumBandwidth.description: Indicates the max bandwidth assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxDCPTCMinimumBandwidth.name: alaDcbxDCPTCMinimumBandwidth
alaDcbxDCPTCMinimumBandwidth.description: Indicates the min bandwidth assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelay.name: alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelay
alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelay.description: PFC link delay allowance. Default for a lossy TC is 0 and cannot be any other value. Default for a lossless TC is 52 and can be changed in a valid range (10-100).

alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelayUserModified.name: alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelayUserModified
alaDcbxDCPTCPFCLinkDelayUserModified.description: Indicates if the Link Delay value has been modified by the user.

alaDcbxDCPTCPFCTrafficFlow.name: alaDcbxDCPTCPFCTrafficFlow
alaDcbxDCPTCPFCTrafficFlow.description: Indicates if PFC traffic flow is enabled on this traffic class

alaDcbxDCPTCPriorityMap.name: alaDcbxDCPTCPriorityMap
alaDcbxDCPTCPriorityMap.description: A bitmap that indicates the priorities assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxDCPTCTrafficScheduler.name: alaDcbxDCPTCTrafficScheduler
alaDcbxDCPTCTrafficScheduler.description: Indicates the traffic class scheduler algorithm assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedBandwidth.name: alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedBandwidth
alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedBandwidth.description: Indicates the recommended min bandwidth assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedTrafficScheduler.name: alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedTrafficScheduler
alaDcbxDCPTCRecommendedTrafficScheduler.description: Indicates the recommended traffic class scheduler algorithm assigned to this traffic class.

alaDcbxPortInstanceTable.name: alaDcbxPortInstanceTable
alaDcbxPortInstanceTable.description: A table of DCP Port Instances.

alaDcbxPortInstanceEntry.name: alaDcbxPortInstanceEntry
alaDcbxPortInstanceEntry.description: A DCP Port Instance Entry. Creating this entry for a port will change the port mode to DCB, set the default DCB profile (if none is specified), will disable NDCB features, and will create a set of alaDcbxPIPrioEntrys for the port.

alaDcbxPIIfIndex.name: alaDcbxPIIfIndex
alaDcbxPIIfIndex.description: Identifier of DCB profile applied to this port.

alaDcbxPIDCBXAdmin.name: alaDcbxPIDCBXAdmin
alaDcbxPIDCBXAdmin.description: DCBX Admin State. Enable or Disable all DCBX features on this port.

alaDcbxPIDCBXOper.name: alaDcbxPIDCBXOper
alaDcbxPIDCBXOper.description: DCBX Oper State. Enable or Disable all DCBX features on this port.

alaDcbxPIAdminDCPId.name: alaDcbxPIAdminDCPId
alaDcbxPIAdminDCPId.description: Identifier of DCB profile applied to this port.

alaDcbxPIAdminDCPName.name: alaDcbxPIAdminDCPName
alaDcbxPIAdminDCPName.description: Name of DCB profile applied to this port.

alaDcbxPILocalModified.name: alaDcbxPILocalModified
alaDcbxPILocalModified.description: Value is true if local configuration is different from configuration imported from the DCB profile applied to this port.

alaDcbxPIPFCDefense.name: alaDcbxPIPFCDefense
alaDcbxPIPFCDefense.description: PFC Defense Mode. Applies when PFC negotiation fails. If value is enabled, then PFC becomes disabled but traffic still flows. If the value is disabled, then PFC local configuration remains on the port.

alaDcbxPIPFCStatsClear.name: alaDcbxPIPFCStatsClear
alaDcbxPIPFCStatsClear.description: Clear the PFC stats for this port.

alaDcbxPIActionTaken.name: alaDcbxPIActionTaken
alaDcbxPIActionTaken.description: Indicates the action taken as a result of the status.

alaDcbxPIRowStatus.name: alaDcbxPIRowStatus
alaDcbxPIRowStatus.description: Controls the creation and deletion of rows in the alaDcbxPortInstanceTable.

alaDcbxPIDCBXVersion.name: alaDcbxPIDCBXVersion
alaDcbxPIDCBXVersion.description: DCBX Version selected on this port.

alaDcbxPIDCBXOperVersion.name: alaDcbxPIDCBXOperVersion
alaDcbxPIDCBXOperVersion.description: DCBX Version operating on this port.

alaDcbxPIDCBXRemoteOperVersion.name: alaDcbxPIDCBXRemoteOperVersion
alaDcbxPIDCBXRemoteOperVersion.description: DCBX Remote Version operating on this port.

alaDcbxPIPriorityTable.name: alaDcbxPIPriorityTable
alaDcbxPIPriorityTable.description: A table of Priorities for DCP Port Instances.

alaDcbxPIPrioEntry.name: alaDcbxPIPrioEntry
alaDcbxPIPrioEntry.description: A DCB profile traffic class entry.

alaDcbxPIPrioPriority.name: alaDcbxPIPrioPriority
alaDcbxPIPrioPriority.description: Indicates the priority of the DCP Port Instance.

alaDcbxPIPrioTC.name: alaDcbxPIPrioTC
alaDcbxPIPrioTC.description: Indicates the traffic class this priority belongs to.

alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesUsed.name: alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesUsed
alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesUsed.description: This object specifies the number of PFC Lossless Priorities in use in the system.

alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesReserved.name: alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesReserved
alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesReserved.description: This object specifies the number of PFC Lossless Priorities in reserved in the system.

alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesAvailable.name: alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesAvailable
alaDcbxPfcLLPrioritiesAvailable.description: This object specifies the number of Priorities available to be configured as PFC Lossless.

alaDcbxPfcUsageTable.name: alaDcbxPfcUsageTable
alaDcbxPfcUsageTable.description: A table of chassis entries. Each depicts the pfc priorities available per chassis. Only valid for TOR platform. In Virtual Chassis mode there is an entry per chassis. In non-Virtual Chassis mode, only one entry is present.

alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesUsed.name: alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesUsed
alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesUsed.description: This object specifies the number of PFC Lossless Priorities in use.

alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesReserved.name: alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesReserved
alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesReserved.description: This object specifies the number of PFC Lossless Priorities reserved.

alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesAvailable.name: alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesAvailable
alaDcbxPfcUsagePrioritiesAvailable.description: This object specifies the number of Priorities available to be configured as PFC Lossless.

alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppT.name: alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppTable
alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppT.description: Table containing entries indicating the status of the corresponding row in lldpXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppTable

alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppE.name: alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppEntry
alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppE.description: Entry that indicates the rowstatus of application priority entry in lldpXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppTable

alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAEPr.name: alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAEPriority
alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAEPr.description: The priority code point that should be used in frames transporting the protocol indicated by alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAESelector and alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAEProtocol

alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppR.name: alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppRowStatus
alaXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppR.description: This object controls only the deletion of an entry in lldpXdot1dcbxAdminApplicationPriorityAppTable.

alaDcbxDCProfileGroup.description: Collection of DCB Profile for management of DCBX.

alaDcbxDCPTrafficClassGroup.description: Collection of DCB Profile Traffic Class for management of DCBX.

alaDcbxPortInstanceGroup.description: Collection of DCP Port Instances for management of DCBX.

alaDcbxPortInstancePriorityGroup.description: Collection of DCP Port Instance Traffic Class for management of DCBX.

alaDcbxPfcUsageGroup.name: alaDcbxPfcUsageGroup
